Chanen Construction Company Names Steve Betts President | Business Wire


























































Chanen Construction Company Names Steve Betts 
      President






Founder Herman Chanen Continues as Chairman and Steven R. Chanen, 
      as CEO










Download



Small


Preview


Thumbnail








Steve Betts is joining the senior leadership team of Chanen Construction Company as president. (Photo: Business Wire)




???pagination.previous???
???pagination.next???







Steve Betts is joining the senior leadership team of Chanen Construction Company as president. (Photo: Business Wire)







Small








Preview








Thumbnail


















Small








Preview








Thumbnail














October 02, 2013 03:15 PM Eastern Daylight Time



PHOENIX--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Chanen Construction Company announced today that Steve Betts, former 
      president and CEO of SunCor Development Company, is joining the senior 
      leadership team as president. He will be responsible for leading new 
      business development in Arizona and across the U.S. Founder Herman 
      Chanen continues in his role as chairman of the 58-year-old construction 
      company, and Steven R. Chanen remains as chief executive officer.
    


      “At Chanen Construction Company, we look forward to the next six decades 
      of success and innovation,” said CEO Steven R. Chanen. “We’re confident 
      in Steve’s leadership and the instrumental role he’ll play in scripting 
      our future. He is a trusted, results-oriented industry professional, who 
      benefits from a likeability factor that is off the charts.”
    

      Known as a leader in real estate development of large-scale office, 
      industrial and mixed-used projects and master planned communities, Betts 
      is also regarded for his work on complex development agreements and 
      economic development projects uniting private, government and 
      institutional interests. Over his 30-year career, Betts has led the 
      development of legislation resulting in the Tourism and Sports Authority 
      Act, the Community Facilities District Act, Development Agreement Act 
      and the Military Airport Authority. In addition, he served as legal 
      counsel and facilitated the creation of important regional landmarks 
      such as the University of Phoenix Stadium in Glendale and Chase Field in 
      downtown Phoenix. As SunCor president and CEO, he led the development of 
      the award-winning Hayden Ferry Lakeside on Tempe Town Lake, a 43-acre 
      urban mixed-use property.
    

      More recently, he served as CEO of PhoenixMart, a 
      1.7-million-square-foot multi-category, manufacturer product-sourcing 
      center, and as senior vice president and managing director of assets for 
      the Arizona State University Foundation.
    

      “Joining Chanen marries my two passions of real estate and economic 
      development,” said Betts. “Building high-quality, job-generating 
      projects is critical to Arizona and regions across the U.S. where Chanen 
      has a presence. The reputation, credibility and competence of Chanen’s 
      team is unrivaled, and I look forward to supplementing their legacy.”
    

      A long-time community steward, Betts is the recipient of numerous awards 
      including Developer of the Year by the Arizona Chapter of the National 
      Association of Industrial and Office Park Developers, Most Admired CEO 
      by the Phoenix Business Journal and Developer of the Year by Southwest 
      Contractor Magazine. He currently serves as chairman of the Urban 
      Land Institute Arizona District Council Governance Committee, a member 
      of the Greater Phoenix Economic Council’s Executive Committee, a member 
      of the Maricopa Association of Government’s Economic Development 
      Committee and chair of the I-11 Coalition.
    

      “When I started this company in 1955, I had two goals: to build 
      important buildings and run a company with smart, ethical and 
      exceptional people,” said board chair, Herman Chanen. “Steve Betts is 
      the epitome of those ideals. His expertise as a real estate developer 
      and strategic insight on economic development concerns will be 
      invaluable to our team.”
    

About Chanen


      Founded in 1955 by Herman Chanen, Chanen Construction Company is an 
      award-winning, full-service construction and construction management 
      organization headquartered in Phoenix and operating throughout the U.S. 
      With an impressive record of successful commercial projects, Chanen is a 
      proven “go-to” builder having completed more than $10 billion of 
      construction work. Chanen’s projects range from education and 
      hospitality to medical and manufacturing. Built on relationships, the 
      company has remained family-owned and operated for 58 years. For more 
      information, visit www.chanen.com 
      or call (602) 266-3600.
    




Contacts

      DRA Strategic CommunicationsDenise D. Resnik, 602-956-8834 x111denise@dracommunications.com














Release Summary
Chanen Construction Company announced today that Steve Betts, former president and CEO of SunCor Development Company, is joining the senior leadership team as president.






Contacts

